.TH OMOHI 1 "" "omohi" "omohi Manual"
.SH NAME
omohi \- local-first CLI for process logging
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B omohi
.RI command " [arguments]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
omohi separates tracking, recording, and referencing so process history remains durable local data.
.PP
This page is generated from src/app/cli/command_catalog.zig. Do not edit manually.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS track
.TP
.B Summary
Register one file or recursively track files under a directory.
.TP
.B Usage
.nf
omohi track <path>...
.fi
.TP
.B Positionals
.RS 4
.B path
required, repeatable: Path to the file or directory to track.
.RE
.TP
.B Examples
.nf
omohi track /tmp/note.txt
omohi track .
omohi track ./*.md
.fi
.TP
.B Notes
.RS 4
The store is auto\-created on the first successful track.
.RE
.RS 4
Directories are expanded recursively into tracked files. Non\-regular entries are skipped.
.RE
.RS 4
Shell\-expanded multiple paths are accepted and processed in order.
.RE
.SS untrack
.TP
.B Summary
Remove one tracked target by ID or clear all missing tracked targets.
.TP
.B Usage
.nf
omohi untrack (<trackedFileId> | \-\-missing)
.fi
.TP
.B Positionals
.RS 4
.B trackedFileId
optional: Tracked file ID from `omohi tracklist`.
.RE
.TP
.B Options
.RS 4
.B \-\-missing
optional: Untrack every tracked entry currently shown as `missing: <absolutePath>` in `omohi status`.
.RE
.TP
.B Examples
.nf
omohi untrack 6b2f0b7309d442f6be405d9dd80e4ad8
omohi untrack \-\-missing
.fi
.TP
.B Notes
.RS 4
Use `omohi tracklist` to resolve IDs before untracking one specific target.
.RE
.RS 4
`\-\-missing` removes all tracked targets that appear as `missing: <absolutePath>` in `omohi status`.
.RE
.RS 4
`<trackedFileId>` and `\-\-missing` cannot be combined.
.RE
.SS add
.TP
.B Summary
Stage one tracked file, a tracked directory subtree, or all changed tracked files.
.TP
.B Usage
.nf
omohi add [\-a|\-\-all] [<path>...]
.fi
.TP
.B Positionals
.RS 4
.B path
optional, repeatable: Path to the tracked file or directory to stage.
.RE
.TP
.B Options
.RS 4
.B \-a, \-\-all
optional: Stage all tracked files shown as `changed: <absolutePath>` in `omohi status`.
.RE
.TP
.B Examples
.nf
omohi add /tmp/note.txt
omohi add .
omohi add ./*.md
omohi add \-a
.fi
.TP
.B Notes
.RS 4
When a directory is given, tracked files under it are staged recursively.
.RE
.RS 4
`\-a` and `\-\-all` stage every tracked file currently shown as `changed: <absolutePath>` in `omohi status`.
.RE
.RS 4
Tracked files shown as `missing: <absolutePath>` in `omohi status` are not staged by `add`; resolve them with `omohi untrack \-\-missing` when needed.
.RE
.RS 4
`\-a` and explicit paths cannot be combined.
.RE
.RS 4
Untracked and non\-regular entries are skipped.
.RE
.RS 4
Shell\-expanded multiple paths are accepted and processed in order.
.RE
.SS rm
.TP
.B Summary
Remove one staged file or recursively unstage staged files under a directory.
.TP
.B Usage
.nf
omohi rm <path>...
.fi
.TP
.B Positionals
.RS 4
.B path
required, repeatable: Path to the staged file or directory to unstage.
.RE
.TP
.B Examples
.nf
omohi rm /tmp/note.txt
omohi rm .
omohi rm ./*.md
.fi
.TP
.B Notes
.RS 4
When a directory is given, staged files under it are unstaged recursively.
.RE
.RS 4
Untracked, non\-staged, and non\-regular entries are skipped.
.RE
.RS 4
Shell\-expanded multiple paths are accepted and processed in order.
.RE
.SS commit
.TP
.B Summary
Create a commit from staged entries.
.TP
.B Usage
.nf
omohi commit \-m <message> [\-t <tag>] [\-\-dry\-run]
.fi
.TP
.B Options
.RS 4
.B \-m, \-\-message <message>
required: Commit message text.
.RE
.RS 4
.B \-t, \-\-tag <tag>
optional, repeatable: Tag name to attach. Can be repeated.
.RE
.RS 4
.B \-\-dry\-run
optional: Show commit result preview without writing commit data.
.RE
.TP
.B Examples
.nf
omohi commit \-m "initial"
omohi commit \-m "release" \-\-tag release \-t prod
omohi commit \-m "check" \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.TP
.B Notes
.RS 4
`\-m` or `\-\-message` is required.
.RE
.RS 4
If a file was already staged and later becomes `missing`, `commit` still uses the staged entry.
.RE
.RS 4
`\-\-dry\-run` shows such staged entries with a `(missing)` marker.
.RE
.SS status
.TP
.B Summary
Show tracked and staged state overview.
.TP
.B Usage
.nf
omohi status
.fi
.TP
.B Examples
.nf
omohi status
.fi
.TP
.B Notes
.RS 4
Human\-readable text output uses one line per entry: `staged: <absolutePath>`, `changed: <absolutePath>`, or `missing: <absolutePath>`.
.RE
.RS 4
`missing` means the path is still tracked but the current file is no longer present as a regular file.
.RE
.RS 4
When `missing` appears, run `omohi untrack \-\-missing` to clear all missing tracked targets explicitly.
.RE
.RS 4
ANSI colors are emitted only when stdout is a TTY.
.RE
